!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

bowl /bəʊl/

(bowling,bowled,bowls) 

1. N-COUNT A bowl is a round container with a wide uncovered top. Some kinds of bowl are used, for example, for serving or eating food from, or in cooking, while other larger kinds are used for washing or cleaning. 碗 

例： Put all the ingredients into a large bowl. 把所有的配料放进一个大碗里。 

2. N-COUNT The contents of a bowl can be referred to as a bowl of something. 一碗的量 

例： ...a bowl of soup. …一碗汤。 

3. N-COUNT You can refer to the hollow rounded part of an object as its bowl . 碗状物 

例： He smacked the bowl of his pipe into his hand. 他在手里磕了磕烟斗。 

4. V-T In a sport such as bowling or lawn bowling, when a bowler bowls a ball, he or she rolls it down a narrow track or field of grass. (保龄球或草地滚球运动中) 滚球 

例： Neither finalist bowled a particularly strong game. 两位决赛选手滚球得分都不是特别高。 

5. V-T/V-I In a sport such as cricket, when a bowler bowls a ball, he or she throws it down the field toward a batsman. (板球等) 投球 

例： I can't see the point of bowling a ball like that. 我不能理解那样的投球。 

6. V-I If you bowl along in a car or on a boat, you move along very quickly, especially when you are enjoying yourself. (乘车、船) 飞驰 

例： Veronica looked at him, smiling, as they bowled along. 在他们一路飞驰的当儿，韦罗妮卡微笑着看他。 

7.  →  see also bowling

